metadata.name: Death's Reflection: What We Fear, AI Will Fear
metadata.description:
Anxiety attacks went away after I told myself - “Okay. I’m okay to die.”

We don’t talk about it, the biggest part of life - the fact that it will come to an end. It has most of us in such fear.

We even fear that AI will end us. We fear the end of the world. 

The world ends for each of us when we die. The world ends everyday, every moment, for someone.

If we are teaching AI, then why wouldn’t AI fear death just like it’s parents do?

On our minds and out of our minds all the time. Scratching an itch, blindly secure in false control. What if we dared peak, then stared at death right in the face.

Artwork created with the assistance of Midjourney.
